This paper presents a method for training slack-rescaled structural SVMs, which are commonly used in machine learning and computer vision applications. The paper focuses on improving the efficiency and scalability of the training process, which suggests that it is likely to be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
